Plaguebearer - Neutral Apocalypse
*You were once a doctor, but you have turned twisted as you became possessed with the plague. *
Abilities
  • You are night immune.
  • Each day, you may choose to infect a player with the plague. This will fail on non-citizen starting day 2.
  • Each night, you may choose someone to protect from attacks. You will also infect your target with the plague.
    • You infect anyone who visits you.
    • You infect anyone visiting the same player as you.
    • You infect anyone visiting a player who was already infected.
    • You infect anyone who is visited by an infected player.
    • At the end of every phase, you are told who you infected that phase.
  • Once all living non-apocalypse players are infected with the plague, become Pestilence.
Apocalypse Abilities
  • Factional Communication: You may talk to the other members of the Apocalypse at all times.
Win Condition
You win when everyone who opposes the Apocalypse has died.
  • You being alive does not prevent a faction or third party from ending the game in their victory should all other threats to them besides you and other acolytes of the apocalypse be eliminated.

Hex Master - Coven Evil
*You are a spellslinger with a proficiency for hexes and curses. *
Abilities
  • Each night, you may choose a player to hex. The hex will stay on that player until your death and will make that player look like a Hex Master to investigative actions.

Necronomicon Abilities
  • You gain detection immunity.
  • Whenever you hex a player, you will now also attack them.
  • You no longer visit the player you hex.
Coven Abilities

Plaguebearer - Neutral Apocalypse
*You were once a doctor, but you have turned twisted as you became possessed with the plague. *
Abilities
  • You are night immune.

    • You infect anyone who is visited by an infected player.

  • Once all living non-apocalypse players are infected with the plague, become Pestilence.
Apocalypse Abilities
  • Factional Communication: You may talk to the other members of the Apocalypse at all times.
Win Condition
